<P>
AFRICA; 
</P>
<P>
MITTERRAND BACKS DEBT RELIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
French President Francois Mitterrand challenged France's Western partners to 
follow Paris' lead in easing Africa's debt burden instead of giving the 
Africans lessons about democracy. In a speech at a Franco-African summit in La 
Baule, France, he announced a symbolic reduction of debt repayments to France 
by four African countries. Mitterrand acknowledged that democratic reform in 
Africa is inevitable, but he cautioned Europe against talking down to Africa. 
</P>
