POLAND; 
</P>
<P>
MUST BE PRESIDENT, WALESA SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lech Walesa said he must become president of Poland to preserve the country's 
failed democracy and prevent his former allies in Solidarity from forming a 
dangerous power monopoly. The union leader challenged his former friends in 
Warsaw who now oppose him to start a separate center-left party and relinquish 
the Solidarity label. 
</P>
