<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALBERTO FUJIMORI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was disappointed in your article on Peru which stated that Sendero Luminoso 
has been responsible for almost 18,000 deaths in the past decade (Part A, June 
11). 
</P>
<P>
This absolves the military and paramilitary from their responsibility in 
thousands of those deaths. While recognizing the fanatical violence of Sendero 
Luminoso, human rights groups, including Amnesty International, have repeatedly 
condemned the Peruvian military's abuses, too. 
</P>
<P>
"Terrorism" is a tactic resorted to by both sides in Peru's so-called 
democracy. 
</P>
<P>
RACHEL BRUHNKE 
</P>
<P>
San Pedro 
</P>
</TEXT>
