<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southern Connecticut Newspapers Inc., a subsidiary of Los Angeles-based Times 
Mirror Co., publisher of The Times, announced that negotiations to acquire 
Acorn Press Inc., publisher of a group of five weekly newspapers serving 
Fairfield County, Conn., have been terminated by mutual agreement . . . 
Burbank-based Walt Disney Co. said it is offering $2.25 billion of Liquid Yield 
Option Notes due 2005. The size of the offering was increased to the 
$2.25-billion principal amount at maturity from $1.5 billion through an 
amendment filed with the SEC. 
