<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAY RESTAURANT CLOSURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Department of Health Services has the power to shut down 
food facilities for as long as necessary for the owners to correct conditions 
that pose a danger to the public health. Here is a list of restaurants closed 
during May. 
</P>
<P>
Archie's Louisiana Seafood -- 4800 S. Normandie Ave., L.A. Closed 5/31 and 
remains closed.* Vermin infestation. 
</P>
<P>
Argentina Restaurant -- 4158 S. Avalon Blvd., L.A. Closed 5/15 and remains 
closed.* No plans submitted. 
</P>
<P>
