<P>
LEGAL ADVISER CHOSEN FOR STATE DEPARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHARLOTTE, N.C. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush will nominate Edwin Williamson to be the new legal adviser of 
the State Department, the White House announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Williamson, who would succeed Abraham Sofaer, has been a partner in the 
national law firm of Sullivan &amp; Cromwell since 1964. 
</P>
