<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 1 ARRESTED IN FIGHTS AT LYNWOOD HIGH SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One youth was arrested but no one was hurt in a spate of fights between 
students at Lynwood High School Wednesday, the last day of the school year, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Of the about 3,000 students on campus, an estimated 100 were involved in the 
approximately 15 brawls that erupted about 1 p.m. outside classes at the 
school, Los Angeles County Sheriff's Sgt. Don Slawson said. 
</P>
<P>
No reason for the violence was immediately clear. 
</P>
<P>
"I think some people were just feeling their oats," Slawson said. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies converged on the campus, "emptying the whole school and 
sending everybody home," Slawson said. Order was restored by about 2 p.m., he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
One youth was arrested, but details were not immediately available. He was not 
identified because of his age. 
</P>
<P>
School officials declined comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
