SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALTADENA; 
</P>
<P>
70 HISTORIC PLACES LISTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tim Gregory, chairman of Altadena Heritage, said Tuesday that the preservation 
group has nearly completed a survey identifying about 70 structures that might 
qualify for the National Register of Historic Places. 
</P>
<P>
When the survey of the eight-square-mile unincorporated area is completed, the 
group intends to request a county ordinance that will protect Altadena's 
historic buildings. It also plans to hold neighborhood meetings that will 
acquaint owners of historic homes with their rights and responsibilities. 
</P>
