<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
SALE OF HOUSING SITE OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Plans for the sale of city-owned property at 471 N. Los Robles Ave. and the 
construction of eight low- and moderate-income housing units on the site was 
approved Tuesday by the Board of Directors. 
</P>
<P>
The parcel will be sold to Villa Los Robles Partners, which will spend $800,705 
to acquire the land and build the project in Northwest Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
The developers will receive a $326,500 loan from the city's Community 
Development Commission. The corporation plans to obtain a conventional loan of 
$354,100 and to invest $120,105 of its own money in the project. 
</P>
<P>
City Director Chris Holden, concerned at the 30-year time period for paying 
back the city loan, asked that city staff members look into ways of speeding up 
repayment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
