<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: POMONA; 
</P>
<P>
AID TO HOMELESS PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has directed its staff to look into ways of funding shelters 
for the homeless and to work with developers of a homeless project that has 
been stymied by city regulations. 
</P>
<P>
George Bosy, who with his business partner, Mike Damico, has converted the Four 
Aces Motel into a refuge for the homeless, asked the council to cut through red 
tape that he said is blocking plans to refurbish and install 10 mobile homes on 
their property. 
</P>
<P>
Bosy said 85 people, most of them formerly homeless, already are living at the 
motel and he would like to use the mobile homes to expand the program. 
</P>
<P>
City officials said Bosy's plan violates city ordinances and would require an 
amendment to the General Plan, new zoning regulations and environmental 
studies. 
</P>
<P>
Bosy said he does not plan a full-scale mobile home park with all the amenities 
that the city would require, but instead is seeking permission to provide basic 
housing for homeless people while they get their lives back in order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
