<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
SCOUTS TO ATTEND CAMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hollywood youngsters from low-income families will have a chance to attend 
Scout camp for a week this summer as part of a program sponsored by the 
Hollywood Sentinels Neighborhood Watch organization. 
</P>
<P>
The Sentinels, a crime watch group since 1988, sponsor a local Boy Scout and 
Girl Scout troop to provide area children with activities designed to keep them 
out of trouble and away from gangs. 
</P>
<P>
Both troops feature weekly meetings and monthly outings for all Scouts, who 
come from the DeLongpre Park area. 
</P>
<P>
This summer, the Sentinels have planned two outings for the Scouts. The Boy 
Scouts will participate in a one-week session at the Los Angeles Council Boy 
Scouts' Lake Arrowhead camps. 
</P>
<P>
Also, the Boy Scouts and Girl Scouts will participate in a one-week excursion 
to the Los Angeles Area Council's Cabrillo Beach Youth Waterfront Sports 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
To help offset the cost of sending children from low-income families, the 
Sentinels are having a rummage sale Saturday from 8:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. at 
DeLongpre Park. From 1 to 2 p.m., the Los Angeles Jazz Society will present its 
Jazz Caravan Concert Series. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call Fares Wehbe at (213) 465-6503 from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
weekdays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
