<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: WEST HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
PLASTIC FOOD PACKAGING BAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council banned the use of food packaging that contains the 
non-biodegradable plastic polystyrene. 
</P>
<P>
Sanctions will range from $100 to $500 in fines and the possible revocation of 
a violator's business license. 
</P>
<P>
Exemptions will include food items packaged outside the city or purchased 
through a contract entered before the effective date of the ban. One-year 
exemptions will be considered for distributors who cannot immediately meet the 
new standard because of "undue hardship." 
</P>
</TEXT>
