<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST : LYNWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
CITY ATTORNEY GIVEN $10 HOURLY HIKE FOR COURT TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Lynwood City Council has approved a $10 increase in hourly litigation rates 
for the city attorney and a $5 hike for his associate. 
</P>
<P>
City Atty. 
</P>
<P>
Henry Barbosa's litigation fee goes from $120 hourly to $130. His associate's 
fee climbs from $110 to $115. The fees apply only when there is special or 
court litigation. Barbosa receives $100 an hour for his regular duties. The fee 
hikes become effective July 1. 
</P>
<P>
During the meeting Tuesday, Mayor Robert Henning announced that Lynwood is one 
of five cities to recently receive a national award from the U.S. Conference of 
Mayors. 
</P>
<P>
The city received the award for establishing the Youth Commission last year. 
The commission is composed of young people who advise the council on programs 
for youths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
