<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BETS: SONGS OF SUMMER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Harmony throughout the World" is the theme for this summer's Camarillo free 
concerts- in-the-park series. The Camarillo Arts Council is bringing myriad 
cultures to Constitution Park. 
</P>
<P>
"This year we have something from every corner of the world, I think, except 
Antarctica," said Rich Smith, coordinator of Sunday's event. 
</P>
<P>
An "Asian-Pacific Music and Dance Festival" begins at 4 p.m. Sunday with a 
Lion's March and five dances representing five regions of China, performed by 
the Ventura County Chinese-American Club. Afterward, advanced students from the 
Tae Ryong Tae Kwon Do School of Camarillo will present a martial arts 
demonstration. A program entitled "Expressions of Polynesia" will conclude the 
program. A variety of dances -- including Hawaiian, Tahitian, Samoan and Mauri 
-- will be presented by Kealoha and Company. 
</P>
<P>
All concerts in the series begin at 4 p.m. Sundays, except one Saturday, Aug. 
18, which begins at 6 p.m.: 
</P>
<P>
July 8 -- The Camarillo Symphony Orchestra will present Shakespeare's "A Comedy 
of Errors." 
</P>
<P>
July 29 -- The Rubin Estrada Band plays Latin jazz and a folkloric dance troupe 
performs. 
</P>
<P>
Aug. 18 -- The Camarillo Symphony Orchestra will return for "Symphony Under the 
Stars" and will be accompanied by Hungarian folk dancers. 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 16 -- A "Scottish Festival" will showcase bagpipers, drummers and 
singers. 
</P>
<P>
The park is at 610 Carmen Drive, Camarillo. Concert-goers are encouraged to 
bring blankets or lawn chairs and a picnic. For information call 987-7847. 
</P>
<P>
Following is a schedule of other free summer programs offered in Ventura 
County. 
</P>
<P>
* The Rancho Simi Park and Recreation District will hold a series in the 
Bicentennial Amphitheater at Rancho Simi Community Park, 1765 Royal Ave., Simi 
Valley: 
</P>
<P>
* A jazz performance by The Irv Johnson Quartet will be from 1 to 4 p.m. 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
* July 22, 2 to 5 p.m. -- "Sounds of the '40s" will be performed by the 
five-piece Big Band Sound. 
</P>
<P>
* Aug. 19, 2 to 5 p.m. Two bands will perform during "Music of the '60s &amp; 
'70s." 
</P>
<P>
For information, call 584-4400. 
</P>
<P>
The Conejo Recreation and Park District is presenting a free program at Conejo 
Community Park, Dover and Hendrix Avenues, Thousand Oaks: 
</P>
<P>
* July 4 -- The Conejo Concert Band will perform patriotic and traditional 
American favorites. 
</P>
<P>
* July 22 -- The Phil Salazar Band entertains with eclectic bluegrass. 
</P>
<P>
* Aug. 5 -- Pop and jazz with Beachfront Property. 
</P>
<P>
* Aug. 19 -- Livingston Taylor performs his hits "I Will Be in Love With You," 
"Loving Arms" and more. 
</P>
<P>
* Sept. 3 -- The Conejo Pops Orchestra performs a repertoire of light classics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
