<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
PROJECT EXEMPT FROM BOND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Board of Directors on Tuesday told One Colorado developer Douglas Stitzel 
that he does not need to put up a "completion bond" on the $70-million retail 
project in Old Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
Stitzel had asked the board to exempt him from the requirement. 
</P>
<P>
His attorney, William Cathey, told the board that the general contractor, C. L. 
Peck/Jones Brothers Construction Corp., already requires that all its 
subcontractors be bonded. 
</P>
<P>
City Directors John Crowley and Rick Cole reminded Cathey that the requirement 
was made in order to guarantee that once work began on the project it would be 
completed. 
</P>
<P>
But Cathey said Stitzel has every intention of completing the job, and will 
secure construction financing within the next two weeks to cover the cost of 
building the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
