<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
POPULAR PUB TO REOPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The former Loch Ness Monster Pub, an Old Pasadena counterculture institution 
closed for the past three months, will reopen Friday under a new name, 
according to the new owners, Martita Titus and Art Jong. 
</P>
<P>
The bar, renamed the Old Pasadena Pub, was to have opened last Friday. 
</P>
<P>
But fire inspectors paid a surprise visit and ordered a number of violations 
corrected, including widening the hallway, installing panic doors on the exits 
and repositioning a wrought iron gate to swing in the opposite direction, Titus 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The pub's previous owners, who closed up shop three months ago in a rent 
dispute with the building's owner, could not be reached for comment. Jong said 
the old owners have told him they plan to reopen elsewhere in Old Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
Titus promises the Old Pasadena Pub will offer the same ambience -- darts, 
dancing and music by Snotty Scotty and The Hankies -- that made the Loch Ness a 
local legend at the corner of Union Street and Fair Oaks Avenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
