<P>
MAJOR LEAGUE TRYOUT CAMP THIS WEEKEND AT OCC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Local baseball players will have a chance to compete in front of scouts from 
many major league baseball teams at a tryout camp Friday and Saturday at Orange 
Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
The camp, which begins at 9 a.m. both days, is sponsored by the Major League 
Scouting Bureau and is open to anyone between the ages of 16 and 25. American 
Legion players must bring a note from their coach with permission to try out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA062190-0140 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 236733 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 21, 1990, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
