<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Leslie Berkman / Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Merger Canceled: Nichols Institute, the medical laboratory firm in San Juan 
Capistrano that is bent on expanding through acquisitions, has retreated from a 
previously announced merger with Pittsburgh-based Med-Chek Laboratories. 
</P>
<P>
Nichols said the companies were "not able to establish mutually satisfactory 
contractual arrangements for the merger" but that Nichols will continue to 
supply services and products to Med-Check, which operates a clinical reference 
laboratory in Pittsburgh and serves customers in the Northeast. 
</P>
