</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Clorox Acquires Pine-Sol Brand: Oakland-based Clorox Co. strengthened its 
stable of household products with the $465-million purchase of Pine-Sol cleaner 
and Combat insecticides from American Cyanamid Co. 
</P>
<P>
The addition of the two brands was expected to boost Clorox's sales by $235 
million a year, the company said. Pine-Sol is the leading brand in the 
$900-million, all-purpose cleaner category. Combat, which sells ant and roach 
killers, is the No. 2 brand in the $450-million insecticide business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
