</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Penny Stock Investors' Law Advances: The House Subcommittee on 
Telecommunications and Finance approved legislation to protect investors who 
buy low-priced "penny stocks" and to crack down on violators of securities 
laws. 
</P>
<P>
One measure would give the SEC more authority to regulate the penny stock 
market and punish manipulative operators. It also would require promoters to 
disclose more information about the stocks and companies they are pushing. Both 
measures now go before the House Committee on Energy and Commerce for 
consideration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
