</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Travelers Quits Nine States: Travelers Corp., which is pulling out of 
California's auto insurance market and has stopped writing new auto policies in 
Pennsylvania, announced that it would also stop offering auto and homeowner 
insurance in nine other states as part of a plan to focus on markets with the 
most potential. The nine states are South Carolina, North Dakota, South Dakota, 
Wyoming, West Virginia, Nevada, Idaho, Arkansas and Oklahoma. A Travelers 
statement suggested that the company wants out of states where it believes 
long-term profitability prospects are poor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
