<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCI OFFERS BREAK FOR SMALL BUSINESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MCI Communications Corp., sharpening its aim at the $18-billion business 
long-distance telephone market, Wednesday unveiled a new package of services 
and discounts for small- and medium-sized businesses. 
</P>
<P>
It said this will give users who spend more than $500 a month on long-distance 
calls some of the same breaks that big telephone customers receive. 
</P>
<P>
"Smaller and mid-sized enterprises represent the largest and fastest-growing 
portion of the commercial telecommunications market," said Timothy Price, MCI 
vice president for general business. 
</P>
<P>
During peak business hours, rates for normal calls will be a flat 20 cents a 
minute. For dedicated access lines, private telephone lines set up by private 
businesses, the rate will be 15 cents a minute. 
</P>
<P>
The new prices are regardless of distance or volume for customers spending $500 
to $50,000 monthly on long-distance services. 
</P>
<P>
MCI said it will also offer a standard 20% discount on telephone calls made 
outside the 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. peak business hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
