<TEXT>
<P>
Environmental Summit: The four television network heads had breakfast Wednesday 
morning -- not to haggle over their competing fall schedules, but to discuss 
the role the entertainment industry has in motivating the public about 
protecting the environment. Bob Iger of ABC, Jeff Sagansky of CBS, Brandon 
Tartikoff of NBC and Peter Chernin of Fox hosted the breakfast seminar at the 
Century City Marriott Hotel in conjunction with the Environmental Media Assn. 
They urged the industry to keep utilizing environmental themes in television 
shows. GREG BRAXTON 
