<HEADLINE>
<P>
CEAUSESCU'S BROTHER GETS 15 YEARS FOR MASS MURDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUCHAREST, Romania 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The brother of executed Romanian dictator Nicolae Ceausescu was jailed for 15 
years today on mass murder charges. 
</P>
<P>
Nicolae Andruta Ceausescu, 66, a former general and head of the secret police 
training school, is the first Ceausescu relative to be convicted in connection 
with attempts to crush last December's anti-Communist uprising in which more 
than 1,000 people were killed. 
</P>
<P>
He was convicted by the Bucharest military court of inciting genocide and of 
"attempted aggravated murder" during the revolt that began in the capital six 
months ago. 
</P>
<P>
The executed Nicolae Ceausescu's son Nicu is also being tried for genocide, and 
his daughter Zoia is in jail awaiting trial for corruption and abuse of 
privilege. 
</P>
<P>
The dictator's sister Maria Agache also went on trial today charged with 
defrauding the state. Several other Ceausescu clan members face similar 
charges. 
</P>
<P>
Nicolae Andruta Ceausescu, who was convicted after almost three months of court 
proceedings, has the right to appeal the sentence within 10 days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
