<P>
BUDDY HOLLY ITEMS ON THE BLOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More contemporary culture will be auctioned off by Sotheby's in New York on 
Saturday when Buddy Holly's personal effects go on the block. 
</P>
<P>
They're being sold to settle a dispute between Holly's wife, Maria Elena, and 
the rest of his family. 
</P>
<P>
The items on sale include Holly's Fender guitar, which has been appraised at 
about $65,000, a pair of red suede shoes, a notebook with handwritten song 
lyrics, a pair of his signature black glasses and an 8-millimeter film of the 
Hollys visiting his hometown, Lubbock, Tex., at Christmas. 
</P>
<P>
"I'd rather have not done this, but what has to be done has to be done," Mrs. 
Holly said of the sale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
